1
00:01:39,479 --> 00:01:40,960
If you're really interested,

2
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:43,020
I suggest reading the original text.

3
00:01:48,720 --> 00:01:49,580
I'm surprised,

4
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:52,840
Mr. Zhuo, you enjoy reading too.

5
00:01:54,479 --> 00:01:58,120
So before going abroad, what did you do here?

6
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:01,520
I majored in Chinese literature in college,

7
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:05,320
and worked at the National Research Institute before going abroad.

8
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:10,240
Then you're quite the scholar of our generation,

9
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:11,560
I'm impressed.

10
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:12,420
You flatter me.

11
00:02:13,480 --> 00:02:16,120
Then your child must be a top student, right?

12
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:17,440
Yes,

13
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:20,800
he graduated from St. Helen University with a computer science degree

14
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:22,060
on a full scholarship.

15
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:54,960
By the way, Professor Zhuo,

16
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:57,690
did you notice Xu Wei's injuries this afternoon?

17
00:02:57,800 --> 00:03:00,460
I don't think those are just ordinary injuries.

18
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:05,060
It looks like domestic violence.

19
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:11,160
Do you think David will show up tonight?

20
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:14,360
I've made myself very clear.

21
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,800
Now it depends on whether David

22
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:18,530
believes that Cui Fengjun will give in tomorrow.

23
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:20,560
Tonight is David's last chance

24
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:21,800
to stop Cui Fengjun.

25
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:24,320
Was that phone call this afternoon

26
00:03:24,320 --> 00:03:25,960
really from Professor Chris?

27
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:27,200
It was an alarm.

28
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:32,120
Hello, Professor Chris.

29
00:03:34,440 --> 00:03:36,120
I was wondering how it could be such a coincidence,

30
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:37,680
that at this critical moment,

31
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:39,400
Cui Fengjun suddenly gave in.

32
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:42,329
I deliberately said those things for him to hear.

33
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:45,140
Did you notice his reaction at that time?

34
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:47,040
Hello, Professor Chris.

35
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:55,200
Really? Cui Fengjun's resistance has decreased?

36
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:59,460
That shows your treatment has been very effective.

37
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:01,120
Good.

38
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:03,120
Okay.

39
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:06,640
You're saying there's more to the story about his attack?

40
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:08,320
I understand.

41
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:13,280
That's great news.

42
00:04:13,880 --> 00:04:17,079
You're hoping for a breakthrough in tomorrow's session.

43
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:19,880
Alright, that's excellent.

44
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:22,760
Looking forward to meeting tomorrow.

45
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:25,640
Okay, goodbye.

46
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:30,020
It seems there's really a turning point.

47
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:35,720
I think he took the bait.

48
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:36,920
Let's hope so.

49
00:04:38,159 --> 00:04:40,159
Now we can only wait for the results.

50
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:41,920
If he shows up tonight,

51
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:44,050
then there's nothing more to discuss.

52
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:46,000
If he doesn't show up,

53
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:49,210
perhaps our judgment was wrong after all.

54
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:08,480
Here.

55
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:11,730
Thank you for helping me so much today.

56
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,000
Don't mention it.

57
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:15,320
Your daughter almost exposed us,

58
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:17,930
fortunately she had a change of heart.

59
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:23,120
You think she's really had a change of heart

60
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:24,520
and stopped opposing me?

61
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:27,920
She probably has some new trick waiting for me.

62
00:05:28,280 --> 00:05:29,600
Don't they say that

63
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:31,880
daughters are their mother's

64
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:33,159
little darlings?

65
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:38,760
In other families, they're darlings,

66
00:05:38,760 --> 00:05:40,720
so why not in mine?

67
00:05:41,960 --> 00:05:43,400
But who can I blame?

68
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:45,159
I chose my husband,

69
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:47,170
and I gave birth to my daughter.

70
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:51,840
That's some deep self-reflection.

71
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:06,440
Come on, tell me about yourself.

72
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,530
What do you mean?

73
00:06:11,320 --> 00:06:13,400
Your spouse has been gone for so long,

74
00:06:13,920 --> 00:06:16,120
and you've been both father and mother,

75
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:18,980
haven't you thought about finding someone new?

76
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:20,490
For my child's sake,

77
00:06:20,960 --> 00:06:21,820
I'd rather not.

78
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:22,840
What's wrong?

79
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:24,960
Afraid your child would object?

80
00:06:28,840 --> 00:06:30,520
Actually, I know that

81
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:34,840
my son has always resented me

82
00:06:35,760 --> 00:06:37,880
because he must have thought

83
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:41,280
I was having an affair,

84
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:43,800
which caused his mother such distress

85
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:46,120
that she became distracted

86
00:06:46,960 --> 00:06:48,220
and had that accident.

87
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:55,620
In that case, it would be hard for your child to accept a new mother.

88
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:01,360
But did you really have an affair back then?

89
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,320
Why are you being so nosy?

90
00:07:05,280 --> 00:07:06,640
So it was true.

91
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:11,120
My impression of you just got worse again.

92
00:07:11,120 --> 00:07:12,800
Why are all men the same?

93
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:16,980
Anyone who hears this would misunderstand.

94
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:18,880
Everyone thinks it was my fault,

95
00:07:18,960 --> 00:07:20,820
let alone a five-year-old child.

96
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:25,480
If you really didn't have an affair,

97
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:27,680
why didn't you explain it to your child?

98
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:29,920
But at that time, the child was so young,

99
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:33,600
only five when he lost his mother.

100
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:37,010
He was already pitiful enough.

101
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:38,480
So...

102
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:40,240
Yes, he was young then,

103
00:07:40,880 --> 00:07:42,800
but how old is he now?

104
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:45,600
Why don't you clear things up?

105
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:47,680
You've been carrying this burden for so long.

106
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:50,880
Some things, if not clarified at the time,

107
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:53,600
may never have a chance to be explained later.

108
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:00,200
That's true.

109
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:04,600
It's always easier to talk about other people's problems,

110
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:08,130
only when it happens to yourself do you know how difficult it is.

111
00:08:09,080 --> 00:08:12,280
Then I can only wish that your name will be cleared soon.

112
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:15,060
I appreciate your kind words.

113
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:17,320
If that day really comes,

114
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:20,000
I hope I'll have the chance to

115
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:21,920
share a drink with you again.

116
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:22,680
Cheers.

117
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:52,400
Mr. Zhuo, someone's coming out.

118
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:53,120
I see them.

119
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:56,480
Is that him? I can't see his face clearly.

120
00:08:56,680 --> 00:08:58,120
I think it is.

121
00:09:03,680 --> 00:09:05,480
That's David's car.

122
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:16,850
They're leaving. Let's follow them quickly.

123
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:53,720
That's not Cui Fengjun.

124
00:09:56,880 --> 00:09:58,800
Could we have been wrong?

125
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:01,360
We can't jump to conclusions yet,

126
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:03,160
let's keep watching for a while.

127
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:06,240
Alright, since our target has appeared,

128
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:09,080
let's keep an eye on him a bit longer.

129
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:27,840
I'm hungry again.

130
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:30,880
So hungry.

131
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:33,400
How about I get you something to eat?

132
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:33,960
Sure.

133
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:37,100
Don't let David out of your sight,

134
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,980
call my cell if anything happens.

135
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:41,260
Don't worry, I'll stay at my post.

136
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:42,160
Alright.

137
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,060
Where's David?

138
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:22,090
Why has he disappeared?

139
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:25,320
Should I go in or not?

140
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:30,760
Right, I can't let him out of my sight.

141
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,560
Where is he?

142
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:24,080
Oh my god! You scared me to death!

143
00:12:27,520 --> 00:12:29,160
Hey, Gu Nian, Gu Nian!

144
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:30,520
What's wrong?

145
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:32,280
I just noticed David was gone

146
00:12:32,280 --> 00:12:33,120
so I went in to find him,

147
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:34,160
but he was in the bathroom,

148
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:36,560
and we nearly bumped into each other face to face.

149
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:38,000
It scared me to death.

150
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:43,320
Are they not leaving anymore?

151
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:45,250
Get in. Let's keep following them.

152
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:38,900
Do you think we might be wrong about this?

153
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:41,980
Let's wait and see.

154
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:50,400
If you're tired, get some sleep.

155
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:51,600
No, no,

156
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:53,860
we agreed to fight this battle together.

157
00:15:07,480 --> 00:15:08,400
Oh no,

158
00:15:09,240 --> 00:15:10,720
I fell asleep?

159
00:15:11,880 --> 00:15:14,540
I've been watching the whole time. Don't worry.

160
00:15:15,160 --> 00:15:16,280
Any developments?

161
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:19,680
He's been at home the whole time, never left.

162
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:23,680
Could it not be him?

163
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,040
I don't know.

164
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:33,240
It's already 6 o'clock.

165
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:34,920
The sun is up.

166
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:38,240
Waiting any longer won't get us anywhere.

167
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:40,170
Let's go back and catch some sleep.

168
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:04,400
Professor Chris.

169
00:16:04,400 --> 00:16:06,880
Zhuopeng, come to the counseling department.

170
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:08,940
Cui Fengjun has been attacked again.

171
00:16:09,040 --> 00:16:10,160
What?

172
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:18,320
Chris, what happened to Cui Fengjun?

173
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:19,400
Have a seat.

174
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:21,320
You look a bit sleep-deprived, don't you?

175
00:16:21,320 --> 00:16:21,960
Yes.

176
00:16:23,520 --> 00:16:24,980
He's been attacked again.

177
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:26,720
Do you have an alibi this time?

178
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:29,250
This could be a good chance to clear your name.

179
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:31,160
Where were you last night?

180
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:32,080
Was anyone with you?

181
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:34,200
Yes, there was.

182
00:16:34,440 --> 00:16:35,640
That's good news.

183
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:38,800
Because Cui Fengjun's testimony keeps changing,

184
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:41,440
the location of the attack, the timeline,

185
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:43,000
and so on keep changing,

186
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:45,320
which really hinders the investigation.

187
00:16:45,320 --> 00:16:47,120
Now that he's been attacked again,

188
00:16:47,120 --> 00:16:48,840
it might actually be good for you.

189
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:50,480
Do you know where he was attacked?

190
00:16:50,480 --> 00:16:51,480
I don't know,

191
00:16:51,880 --> 00:16:55,010
but everything I'm telling you is insider information.

192
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:57,040
I understand.

193
00:16:57,800 --> 00:16:58,680
Thank you.

194
00:16:59,080 --> 00:16:59,960
Bye.

195
00:17:01,480 --> 00:17:02,200
Chris.

196
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:05,000
Do you know where Cui Fengjun is now?

197
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:06,930
He's taken leave and is at home now.

198
00:17:08,880 --> 00:17:11,280
Are you awake? I'm coming to pick you up now.

199
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:12,930
We need to find Cui Fengjun.

200
00:17:31,680 --> 00:17:33,940
We have something important to tell you.

201
00:17:40,840 --> 00:17:42,760
Teacher Zhuo was beaten so badly.

202
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:45,760
Talk.

203
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:49,200
This time you can't say I was the one who beat you, right?

204
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:50,330
I don't understand.

205
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:56,280
I'm sorry that you got beaten by David again because of me.

206
00:17:56,280 --> 00:17:58,320
Who said David beat me?

207
00:17:58,320 --> 00:18:00,360
I deliberately told David

208
00:18:00,840 --> 00:18:02,160
that you might give in

209
00:18:02,440 --> 00:18:04,040
and reveal who attacked you.

210
00:18:06,280 --> 00:18:07,080
I understand.

211
00:18:07,080 --> 00:18:09,480
Why did David say I was going to betray him?

212
00:18:09,640 --> 00:18:10,920
So it really was David who beat you?

213
00:18:10,920 --> 00:18:11,840
Who else?

214
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:13,620
We were just guessing before.

215
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:14,840
You guys

216
00:18:16,520 --> 00:18:17,280
are clever.

217
00:18:19,520 --> 00:18:20,720
So you're admitting

218
00:18:21,080 --> 00:18:23,720
that David was the one who beat you both times.

219
00:18:23,920 --> 00:18:26,400
You're the ones who hurt me.

220
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:27,680
We hurt you?

221
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:30,360
You were the one sending harassing emails to Xu Wei,

222
00:18:30,360 --> 00:18:32,320
all of this is your own doing.

223
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:34,130
Not just harassing emails,

224
00:18:34,360 --> 00:18:36,720
you must have done something worse.

225
00:18:39,360 --> 00:18:40,760
You insulted Xu Wei

226
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:43,920
specifically about her marrying a white man.

227
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:45,920
David has already called the police

228
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:49,240
and demanded you undergo mandatory psychological treatment.

229
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:51,320
He didn't attack you because of that.

230
00:18:53,560 --> 00:18:55,020
Actually, you were beaten

231
00:18:55,040 --> 00:18:56,680
because you refused to stop.

232
00:18:57,200 --> 00:18:59,600
Instead, you escalated by stalking Xu Wei.

233
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:01,960
But you didn't expect

234
00:19:02,360 --> 00:19:05,490
that you would discover Xu Wei's domestic abuse secret.

235
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:15,460
You even used this to threaten Xu Wei,

236
00:19:15,760 --> 00:19:18,680
which is what led David to attack you.

237
00:19:18,680 --> 00:19:20,240
It seems David

238
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:22,320
really did hit Xu Wei.

239
00:19:29,640 --> 00:19:30,640
I insulted Xu Wei.

240
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:33,320
Fine, my fault.

241
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:34,520
David.

242
00:19:35,640 --> 00:19:37,120
Good person, good man.

243
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:40,200
Goes home and beats his wife.

244
00:19:40,960 --> 00:19:42,080
Psycho.

245
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:48,620
But you didn't expect David would come looking for you.

246
00:19:52,360 --> 00:19:53,600
No, I didn't.

247
00:19:54,320 --> 00:19:57,920
He's terrifying.

248
00:20:26,840 --> 00:20:28,700
Are there any other memory cards?

249
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:34,240
Okay.

250
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:36,680
I believe you.

251
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:40,760
But if I find out

252
00:20:40,760 --> 00:20:42,440
that you've lied to me,

253
00:20:42,840 --> 00:20:45,640
the punishment won't be limited to today's scale.

254
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:55,680
If I expose you,

255
00:20:56,040 --> 00:20:58,920
you won't get away with it either.

256
00:20:59,720 --> 00:21:01,520
I have nothing to fear.

257
00:21:01,680 --> 00:21:03,120
I'm just a student,

258
00:21:03,760 --> 00:21:06,640
while you're a renowned biologist.

259
00:21:07,560 --> 00:21:12,440
You not only abuse your wife and assault students,

260
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:13,880
you'll go to prison.

261
00:21:17,240 --> 00:21:18,900
You reminded me of something.

262
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:21,850
You're a third-year biology student, right?

263
00:21:23,360 --> 00:21:25,490
What are your plans after graduation?

264
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:31,640
If you plan to continue in biology or pharmaceuticals

265
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:34,280
down this career path,

266
00:21:34,280 --> 00:21:36,240
then you'll definitely run into me.

267
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:38,920
Now, if you behave yourself,

268
00:21:39,080 --> 00:21:40,410
there will be benefits.

269
00:21:42,480 --> 00:21:43,480
Otherwise...

270
00:21:46,440 --> 00:21:48,200
You're a smart person.

271
00:21:50,520 --> 00:21:51,920
You understand.

272
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:11,120
I remember now.

273
00:22:11,120 --> 00:22:12,560
That day in the counseling department,

274
00:22:12,560 --> 00:22:15,080
you were terrified when you saw Professor Zhuo.

275
00:22:15,080 --> 00:22:17,840
Actually, you weren't afraid of Professor Zhuo at all,

276
00:22:17,840 --> 00:22:19,800
but of David standing behind him.

277
00:22:21,040 --> 00:22:23,240
So you were afraid of David at that time.

278
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:36,560
Fine, I understand why you won't testify against him,

279
00:22:36,560 --> 00:22:38,200
but why frame me?

280
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:42,960
I don't like you.

281
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:44,960
